image.altText: Collingwood AFL player Nick Daicos stands wearing a tuxedo next to a woman in a pink dress before the Brownlow Medal ceremony.

props.synopsis: Nick Daicos is eyeing a slice of Brownlow Medal history, but will have to hold off the likes of Marcus Bontempelli and Lachie Neale to claim the AFL's highest individual honour. Follow live.

title.children: Stars arrive for Brownlow Medal count with Daicos, Bontempelli among the favourites

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: We're expecting Gillon McLachlan to begin the count at 8:05pm AEST, and the winner should be confirmed by 10:45pm AEST. A long night ahead, so I'm going to need you to keep me company in the comments with your thoughts and feelings through the night. In the mean time, here's probably the most athletically gifted couple at the Brownlow tonight — Adam Treloar and Kim Ravaillion.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Nick and partner Araette Jones are officially in the building, and you can bet there will be cameras pointed at the two of them all evening. Daicos is a hot favourite to become the youngest Brownlow winner in 30 years, with seemingly only a late-season injury standing between him and the medal. It's going to be thrilling to see if Nick can build enough of a lead early in the season to hold off the challengers late.
